Newcastle is set to sign  France 
fullback Mathieu Debuchy after agreeing to a fee of about 5
million pounds ($8.1 million) with French soccer club Lille, Sky
Sports reported.  The 27-year-old will join the Magpies next month during the
mid-season transfer window subject to personal terms and passing
a medical examination,  Sky Sports said .  Real Madrid and Inter Milan had also been interested in
signing Debuchy, Sky Sports added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
